### Wave A — Trust & clarity (ship blockers)

1. PR1 — Icon fixes + dead alias cleanup + `AppIconsTest`
2. PR2 — Semantic text colors (`InkSecondary`), contrast tokens, complete typography scale
3. PR3 — `JourneyButton` / `JourneyTextField` / `JourneyIconButton` (focus, `isError`, `supportingText`, 56dp min height, 16dp field spacing)
4. PR4 — `JourneyLoading` / `JourneyError` / `JourneyEmpty` + i18n
5. PR5–8 — Screen migrations (grocery → home → meal plan → household → auth/account)
6. PR9 — Touch-target instrumented tests + Firebase QA YAML

### Wave B — Mobile polish (post-beta)

7. PR10 — Snackbar anchor above `bottomBar` (`NutritionScaffold` padding helper); grocery undo flow QA
8. PR11 — Inline form validation (login, join/OTP `isError` on field, rename household)
9. PR12 — Haptics via `expect fun performJourneyHaptic()` (Android first; no-op on iOS until wired)
10. PR13 — `AnimatedContent` route transitions in `App.kt` (subtle horizontal slide)
11. PR14 — Pull-to-refresh on grocery + meal plan (sync with `NutritionScreenModel.refresh`)
12. PR15 — List row ergonomics: `heightIn(min = 56.dp)` on dense rows; collapsible chevron rotation

### Wave C — Platform breadth (product decision)

13. Dark theme — brand `darkColorScheme` + system follow (defer until light polish done)
14. Window size classes — two-column meal plan / grocery on `width > 600dp`
15. AI read-only accent — optional terracotta tint on `AiReadOnlyGroceryList` wrapper (cards already have `FamilyLogisticsCardSurface` border)

### Already in good shape (do not regress)

- **Back navigation:** `BackHandler` in `App.kt`; `NutritionScaffold` back icon uses `Res.string.action_back` as `contentDescription`
- **Invite deep links:** `InviteRedirectUrls` + `MainActivity` intent handling + `InviteJoinFlowCoordinator`
- **Locale parity:** `*LocaleStringsTest` in `commonTest/kotlin/.../i18n/` (5 suites)
- **AI read-only separation:** `AiReadOnlyGroceryList` uses `FamilyLogisticsCardSurface` + sparkles + subtitle

### Text color rule (Review 2)

Prefer `SharedJourneyColors.InkSecondary` (add in PR2) over `InkDeep.copy(alpha = 0.65f–0.75f)` for subtitles and hints — alpha stacking fails contrast on glass surfaces.

### Form ergonomics defaults (`JourneyTextField`)

- Min height 56dp; 16dp vertical spacing between fields
- `isError` + `supportingText` for validation (errors below field, not only screen-level `Text`)
- IME: `Next` on intermediate fields, `Done` on last field, `Go`/`Send` on single-field submit
